Preheat your oven to 220°C. Boil a full kettle.

Put the @soy sauce{15%ml} and @sugar{2%tsp} into a #medium bowl{} and mix together.

Add the @British chicken thighs{3} to the bowl and turn to coat evenly.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lay the chicken onto lightly oiled #baking tray{} and spoon over any remaining soy mixture from the bowl.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until browned and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiling water into a #large saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @pak choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways.

Heat a drizzle of @oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and fry for ~{2%minutes}.

Add the @coleslaw mix{150%g} and pak choi to the mushrooms with a drizzle more @oil if needed.

Stir-fry until the veg has softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @bulgogi sauce{150%g}, then bring to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat.

> If you've added prawns to your meal, add them to the pan when you add the veg and coleslaw mix. Stir-fry with the veg until cooked through, 4-5 mins. Then add the garlic and bulgogi sauce and continue. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, slice thinly and add to the pan with the veg, along with any soy glaze from the tray.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and spoon into your bowls.

Top with the bulgogi veg and soy baked chicken.

Roughly chop and sprinkle over the @salted peanuts{25%g} to finish. Enjoy!